Laudrup to Move to Chelsea 
Danish winger Brian Laudrup was set to sigh for Chelsea after his
contract with Scottish club Rangers expired at the end of the season,
newspapers in England and Denmark reported Thursday.
Laudrup agreed a three-year deal with the Stamford Bridge club worth
around 50,000 pounds a week, the Daily Mirror said.
Newly promoted Chelsea player-manager Gianluna Vialli held talk with
Laudrup in London last week before the Italian succeeded sacked boss
Ruud Gullit of Netherlands.
Bladet Rangers sources had confirming the move would go ahead,
according to the Danish paper Extra.
Laudrup has also been linked with moves to Ajax and Manchester United
before.
